Package it.polimi.se2019.server.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Drawable
    This marker interface implements methods for weapons and loot cards and power ups.
    Grabbable
    This interface describes the behaviour of weapons and loot cards, which are both elements that can be grabbed on the map.
    Jsonable
    This interface is implemented by all elements that are generated through a JSON file.
    PlayerValue
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    Targetable
    This interface gathers methods that tiles and players have in common as both can be considered as targets of weapons or power ups.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Action
    This class describes the single actions that can be done when using a weapon.
    Ammo
    This class defines an ammo which consists of its colour.
    Card
    This class consists of a generalization of power up and weapon.
    Combo
    This class defines the combos that can be used by the player throughout the game, for instance Run Around, Grab Stuff, Shoot People,..
    ComboHelper
    Combo helper generates all the available combos Combo from a JSON file.
    Deck
    This class generalizes all the decks used in the game and it contains both a regular deck and one with all the discards as those can be used whenever the regular deck is over.
    Effect
    This abstract class implements a generic effect of a card.
    Figure
    This class defines the figures of the game.
    FinalFrenzyBeforeFirst
    This class implements the state pattern.
    FinalFrenzyStandard
    This class implements the state pattern.
    FirstDeath
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    Game
    This class communicates with the virtual view.
    GameMap
    This class defines the map used throughout the game.
    GenericWeaponEffect
    This class extends the Effect class Effect by adding useful properties such as the price of the weapon or power up effect.
    GraphNode<T>
    This class implements a generic graph that contains a set of children and parents.
    GraphWeaponEffect
    This class extends Generic Weapon Effect GenericWeaponEffect by adding a partial effect to it.
    Healthy
    This class defines a healthy player that was hit 0, 1 or 2 times.
    JsonHelper
    This class is a general helper for all JSON generated helpers: WeaponHelper, PowerUpHelper, ComboHelper, ComboHelper
    KillshotTrack
    This class implements the killshot track in which all the kills are stored.
    LootCard
    This class defines loot cards, which can be grabbed on loot tiles.
    LootCardHelper
    This class generates Loot Cards and retrieves cards parsing their name.
    LootTile
    This class defines a loot tile, its grabbable is a loot card.
    MapConfig
    This class defines the map that are built form the JSON files.
    MatchStarted
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    MoreDeaths
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    NoDeaths
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    PartialWeaponEffect
    This class extends Effect and describes a partial effect, which is part of a Weapon Effect.
    Player
    This class implements the player of the game.
    PlayerDamage
    This class implements a state pattern thanks to which it is possible to add new moves to a damaged player.
    PowerUp
    This class defines a power up, which is generated by a JSON in PowerUpHelper PowerUpHelper.
    PowerUpHelper
    This class generates the Power Up from the JSON files present in the given directory.
    SecondDeath
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    Skull
    This class defines a skull which is empty until a user dies.
    SlightlyDamaged
    This class defines a player that was hit between 3 and 5 times.
    SpawnTile
    This class extends the Tile class Tile and is grabbables are weapon that make up a weapon spot.
    TargetSpecification
    This class defines the properties targets need to have in order to be hit by each weapon.
    Tear
    This class defines a tear, which represents the damage or mark element given by a player to another.
    ThirdDeath
    A state pattern implements the lowering of the value of a certain player (points-wise) whenever they die.
    TickingTimer
    This class implements a timer whose duration can be set.
    Tile
    This class implements the tiles of the game map.
    TurnMemory
    This class stores hit targets and tiles as some weapons have a memory and their targets vary depending on the targets or tiles hit during a specific effect.
    VeryDamaged
    This class defines a player that was hit 6 times or over.
    Weapon
    This class implements the weapons created dynamically through the WeaponHandler WeaponHelper.
    WeaponEffect
    This class extends a generic effect and adds a set of partial weapon effects to it.
    WeaponHelper
    This class generates all the available weapons fetching their JSONs from the defined folder of weapons.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ActionType
    This enum defines the type of actions that can be done while using a weapon or a power up.
    AmmoColour
    This enum defines the allowed colours for ammos.
    Direction
    This enum defines the possible directions of movements.
    FigureColour
    This enum defines the possible colours the figures can have.
    PartialCombo
    This enum defines the atomic actions that can be used to build a combo Combo in any phase of the game and with any damage.
    RoomColour
    This enum defines the possible colours each room can have.
